gui.model.domain

Enum ComponentInfoType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ComponentInfoType>
      • gui.model.domain.ComponentInfoType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ComponentInfoType>

    public enum ComponentInfoType
extends java.lang.Enum<ComponentInfoType>
    Represents the basic categories of components based on what domain-relevant information can be extracted from them.
    Author:
    Michaela Bacikova, Slovakia, michaela.bacikova@tuke.sk

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • FUNCTIONAL

        public static final ComponentInfoType FUNCTIONAL
        A group including all functional components in the target application GUI. Functional components represent the basic functionalities of the application and they enable actions which change the application state.
        If we remove general functionalities such as "Save as..", "Open", "New" etc., we can extract application domain functionalities.
        Examples: buttons, web-links, menus, file choosers.

      • DESCRIPTIVE

        public static final ComponentInfoType DESCRIPTIVE
        A group including all informative and textual components in the target application GUI.
        Informative and textual components have the ability to display or acquire data or to determine a purpose of another components.
        Example: labels, spinner, text components (text areas, text fields, etc.), tree, graph, picture image

      • TEXTUAL

        public static final ComponentInfoType TEXTUAL

      • LOGICALLY_GROUPING

        public static final ComponentInfoType LOGICALLY_GROUPING
        A group including all logically grouping components. Logically grouping components are components which components or content related logically.
        Examples: combo box, list, radio button group, check box group, tree, tabbed pane

      • CONTAINERS

        public static final ComponentInfoType CONTAINERS
        A group including all graphically grouping components. Graphically grouping components related graphically (and/or logically).
        Examples: container, tabbed pane, menu, window, dialog, panels

      • SEPARATORS

        public static final ComponentInfoType SEPARATORS
        Separators divide groups of components into logically related subgroups.

      • CUSTOM

        public static final ComponentInfoType CUSTOM
        Custom components are components created by programmers.
        When a programmer creates a new custom component, he inserts new terms into the application language.
        The amount of domain information possible to extract from such a component depends on the component implementation.
        If the component is created incorrectly, then it is hard or impossible to extract domain information from it. To handle such components, new DomainIdentifiable handler has to be created.

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final ComponentInfoType UNKNOWN
        If a component can not be included into any of these groups, then it is of information type UNKNOWN.
